-- storage.sql
--
-- !! DO NOT EDIT THIS FILE DIRECTLY !!
--
-- This file is superseded by migrations/storage.default.sql.
--
-- During  npm run setup  the setup wizard reads storage.default.sql, replaces
-- the REPLACE_WITH_STORAGE_BUCKET placeholder with the user-chosen bucket name,
-- and runs the resulting SQL directly via the Supabase Management API.
-- This file is never read on disk by the migration runner.
--
-- • For Supabase Storage: the RLS policies are generated from storage.default.sql
--   using your configured STORAGE_BUCKET value.
-- • For Cloudflare R2: this migration is skipped entirely (R2 manages its own
--   permissions outside Supabase).
--
-- To re-apply storage policies manually, copy storage.default.sql, replace
-- REPLACE_WITH_STORAGE_BUCKET with your bucket name, and run via the Supabase
-- SQL Editor or Management API.
